betterquesting.name: Gather remains
betterquesting.desc: Check the place for items

betterquesting.name: Farm in a box
betterquesting.desc:
We dont have the time to work on the field, we need to put this farm in a box we found in the base to some use!

I hope we have some water in the storage...

betterquesting.name: Nothing matters to you
betterquesting.desc:
Does it even matter?

I fear the mainframe has loaded wrong data fragments into my core. My communication module is failing alot.

Anyway. Get more matter!

betterquesting.name: Time to analyze that matter!
betterquesting.desc: Im pretty sure we can find some hard matter we can use for construction or similiar!

betterquesting.name: I call timber!
betterquesting.desc: This little box seems to be able to even grow trees. Is there some kind of pocket dimension in it?

betterquesting.name: Matter Manipulation
betterquesting.desc: Breaking things down into elements is crucial to our survival! But we need a more potent source of matter!

betterquesting.name: Heat it up!
betterquesting.desc: If you wonder what you could use to smelt the stone ... check the crashsite!

betterquesting.name: Si is so usefull!
betterquesting.desc: Lets try to break down some of the Obsidian we made!

betterquesting.name: STOP! Hammertime!
betterquesting.desc:
Uhhuuu uhoooo uhuu whoooo ... *static noise*

Oh im sorry! Just scanned some files in my system in a folder called "glorious 80-90"

Well we need matter. That means : YOU need to get some matter. Maybe this will help you ...

betterquesting.name: Remember to keep breathing
betterquesting.desc: The base seems to have a life support system. Theres a small screen showing ice and snow on it.

betterquesting.name: Traces of metal
betterquesting.desc: Time to get your head banging! We can smelt the broken traces we found!

betterquesting.name: Breaking down
betterquesting.desc: One of the easiest forms of matter manipulation is breaking things down. We need a machine for that!

betterquesting.name: Merging it back
betterquesting.desc: We need another machine to merge matter together! Chemistry! #wearegavi

betterquesting.name: Assembly required!
betterquesting.desc: Time to fire up the assembly machine!

betterquesting.name: Combining it
betterquesting.desc: Now that we can manipulate matter with the decomposer and the synth, we should be able to create some basic building materials!

betterquesting.name: Refined coal
betterquesting.desc: The decomposer seems to better work with liquified coal. (Warning, dont pipe it directly into the decomposer)

betterquesting.name: Cracking it down
betterquesting.desc: The assembly chamber has a blueprint for a machine that will improve our metal yields.

betterquesting.name: Faster machines
betterquesting.desc: Its time to upgrade the machines we have. I suggest starting with the farm in a box.

betterquesting.name: Essence of life
betterquesting.desc: With the farming module we can multiply foods. Foods contain water. Water can be transmuted to snow... breathable air.... life...

betterquesting.name: Molten Stone
betterquesting.desc:
I found some old plans for a machine that can produce matter out of lava and water. This might become usefull!

You can get bonemeal and clay by analyzing matter in the siev... ahem .. analyzing chamber!

betterquesting.name: All ways lead to iron
betterquesting.desc: One important thing you should know about this strange universe is that there are usually different ways with different yields for matter manipulation. You should take a close look at whats the most efficient and what processes you can afford.

betterquesting.name: Unlocking the powercore
betterquesting.desc:
The bases system needs a large amount of power to restart its subsystems.

Warning : Try to get enough energy first to discharge directly into the submission unit. Changes in the submission power system can lead to a (rare) quest reset.

betterquesting.name: Restoring systems
betterquesting.desc:
We have the basic matter manipulation and chemistry systems online.

I can now try to restore the more advanced systems.

Rerouting power....
Standby...
Failure...
Analysing...

Oh its simple! I have no power I can reroute.

You need to manually power my mainframe. To do this you must create an interface first. Hope you saved some Keratin.

betterquesting.name: Where ever your life takes you
betterquesting.desc: It hands you lemons. Umh I mean Potatoes.

betterquesting.name: Retinol
betterquesting.desc: Theres more potent stuff out there. Lets start with carrots!

betterquesting.name: Refined Fuel
betterquesting.desc:
Power will become a big thing for us soon.

Theres quite some options avaible but the fuel is special. You can often refine it into cleaner states that will yield in better power. Lets start with breaking down coal and wood.

betterquesting.name: Automating the synthesizer
betterquesting.desc:
You may have noticed already. Those export bus are stupid! Filling up the whole synthesizer with one single item.

We have a fix for this. The rationing pipe! It makes sure that connected transfer pipes only put in one stack of an item.

betterquesting.name: More Water
betterquesting.desc: Our water usage is increasing. Especially when we break it down for oxygen. The reconstruction of trees in the farm-in-a-box will do for a while until we find a better solution to this.

betterquesting.name: Lindsey has power!
betterquesting.desc:
Our solar base power is quite nice.

Anyways we should improve our power generation and put our new fuels to some use!

betterquesting.name: Buildingaid
betterquesting.desc: The projector and the blueprint will help you build the chemistry multiblocks. Make sure you have enough space!

betterquesting.name: Roll roll roll ... roll the ingot ...
betterquesting.desc: To further process the plates and ingots we could use a metal former.

betterquesting.name: Seperate!
betterquesting.desc: Fusion and Fission are two main concepts of chemical matter manipulation. We should create a fission reactor so we can breakdown hoarded materials in maybe something usefull to create energy.

betterquesting.name: Unite!
betterquesting.desc: With this totally inexpensive and small machine we can create whatever we need!

betterquesting.name: More effective ways
betterquesting.desc: We need to improve our yields from those traces. I think chemistry can help here!

betterquesting.name: Shiny Captain!
betterquesting.desc: Carbon ... a basic element of our surroundings. We can transform it into something precious!

betterquesting.name: Speeding up the assembly
betterquesting.desc: Ridiculous amounts of energy need to be transfered to our assembly table. We should add some lasers!

betterquesting.name: STOP the hammertime!
betterquesting.desc: Its tedious to swing that hammer, isnt it? Well I found a blueprint for something usefull!

betterquesting.name: Transferring it to the machine
betterquesting.desc: Okay this sounds absolute crazy and must be some medieval magic. You need to transfer the knowledge on a diamond pickaxe, then use another machine to transfer it to the receiving machine.

betterquesting.name: Another assembly machine
betterquesting.desc: Our standardissue assembly machine works great, but sometime you need something bigger!

betterquesting.name: Meow
betterquesting.desc: Finally we need the receiving machines. Lets start with a laser for our assembly chamber.

betterquesting.name: Diamonds and pearls
betterquesting.desc: I found a strange assembly recipe in my datacores and uploaded it to the assembly chamber. Its quite energy hungry but data indicates it can help with the assembly energy transfer systems.

betterquesting.name: Fortune
betterquesting.desc: I think you already know what to do....

betterquesting.name: Efficiency
betterquesting.desc: Secret knowledge to improve things can be written into a special book by the lasers of our assembly chamber! Many "plus items" work way better than the standard parts when they get enchanted!

betterquesting.name: Quarry²
betterquesting.desc: We can also build better excavation systems now!

betterquesting.name: gOil
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Slicly
betterquesting.desc: Raw ingots and blocks will do no good when we want advanced items. We should make plates. Alot. A truckload. Several. Well you get the idea...

betterquesting.name: Chemical foundations
betterquesting.desc: We need so much matter, we better make a machine that can supply us with plenty of silicon.

betterquesting.name: Green Water
betterquesting.desc: This should suffice until we find a natural water source.

betterquesting.name: Casting molten metal
betterquesting.desc: This more elegant treatment of precious metals increases the yield.

betterquesting.name: Get in shape
betterquesting.desc: The caster also needs molds. Some designs are saved in our assembly chamber, others must be crafted by hand.

betterquesting.name: Moar machines!
betterquesting.desc: Now that we have the processor production running we can make alot of new machines! The foundation for them is the ...

betterquesting.name: SWAG Mill!
betterquesting.desc: We need silicon, lots of silicon. A swaggy mill will help with that. We could either simply use sand or look for a way to mass produce clay blocks.

betterquesting.name: Stamp!
betterquesting.desc: Processors need to be stamped into raw printed samples and then combined into something actually usefull.

betterquesting.name: Testdriving the inscribers
betterquesting.desc: Lets see if we have everything together for mass production!

betterquesting.name: Processors!
betterquesting.desc:
I have a feeling we will need alot of processors. I found blueprints for a computing unit thats based on metal and quartz.

We should start by refining the quartz we found on mars.

betterquesting.name: Patterns and presses
betterquesting.desc: Those inscribers need to have a press plate!

betterquesting.name: License to plate
betterquesting.desc: What do we want? Plates! And when do we want them? Naow!

betterquesting.name: Incremental Inception
betterquesting.desc: What are you hoarding for? Make hulls!

betterquesting.name: Incremental is fun!
betterquesting.desc: Yo dawg! I put a plate in your plate so you can ... I mean ... we can compress them to be even more durable!

betterquesting.name: Im a rocket man!
betterquesting.desc: Okay. I have an ancient alien station and an artificial intelligence. But seems that my travel options are quite limited. Lets build something archaic to get to the mars!

betterquesting.name: Give me fuel
betterquesting.desc:
Give me fire,
Give me that which I desire,
Ooh!

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Queen of the
betterquesting.desc: .. umh well. Gas station. We need one to fill the rocket.

betterquesting.name: Foundation
betterquesting.desc: Rocket goes on top!

betterquesting.name: Cobble it up
betterquesting.desc: This will make our extruders way more efficient on usage and output! We should make this as soon as possible and maybe even make the second augment!

betterquesting.name: Power transfer
betterquesting.desc: For your starting needs, just use the smallest EIO conduits. The upgraded versions wont do you any good.

betterquesting.name: No limits
betterquesting.desc:
We reach for the sky! No valley too deep. No mountain too high!

Well these "little" cables can transfer an unlimited amount of RF. You will definitly need them in this pack!

betterquesting.name: Maybe not skip reading this time
betterquesting.desc:
You use the rocket to fly tomars.

You really should bring along : A Warp scroll bound at a waystone home (to get back to the moon). Else you need the infrastructure and power to refuel the rocket on the mars to fly back. The Waystone is the easy mode. 

You could die on the mars. So its a good idea to bring another Waystone, bind some warpscrolls there and then send them along with the rocket back to the moonbase via an enderchest you brought along.

This could prevent alot of tears, but well, you are a free person with free choices ;)

betterquesting.name: Na desh hat ja geklappt!
betterquesting.desc: So you made it to mars and found desh. Great! We can now start to build advanced machines!

betterquesting.name: Seeds of love
betterquesting.desc:
Sowing the seed of loooooove.... seeeeds of loooooove.

Oh sorry. I really need to delete that strange data cluster with the antique music.

Anyways. Could you make some seeds? I have a feeling we will need alot of them.

betterquesting.name: Gallium, as small village in france
betterquesting.desc: New ways to get materials we desperatly need for the new technologies!

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Replicator online
betterquesting.desc: You did it! I have reconstructed the replication chamber with the provided energy. Now we can start making things out of ... more energy. Well to be honest. MUCH more energy!

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Mark 3
betterquesting.desc: Dont forget to wave to Mark when you pass Mars and travel into the unknown!

betterquesting.name: Conversion
betterquesting.desc:
So many mods in the sky!

Due to the nature of some mods its sometimes important to have the "correct tin block".

Thats why we have a manual and an automatic oredictionary converter. So you can convert stuff between mods however you need them. The manual one works like chisel and you simply convert into what you need. The automatic one needs to be pre-programmed with the target and can be automated afterwards.

betterquesting.name: Time is ticking
betterquesting.desc: Some materials need to be handled very carefully

betterquesting.name: IKEA in a box
betterquesting.desc:
Some assembly required ... so ... let's make an assemblya machine!

You might notice those techreborn machines dont like EIO conduits. And later the EIO conduits dont transfer enough energy, so better get used to the REAL GOOD pipes!

betterquesting.name: Stoned
betterquesting.desc: Compressing stone ... alot! This little machine can also compress other materials. Quite handy!

betterquesting.name: Workout
betterquesting.desc: A stick and two Bedrockium ingots ... there's your personal gym!

betterquesting.name: Do you even lift bro?
betterquesting.desc: Whats even more heavy than Bedrockium ingots? Plates! We love plates!

betterquesting.name: Another great instrument
betterquesting.desc: Good for percussions. Or liquid storage.

betterquesting.name: Through the nether
betterquesting.desc: STARring metal.

betterquesting.name: Mother of hulls
betterquesting.desc: This one is quite expensive to make. But dont worry, we still have more expensive stuff!

betterquesting.name: Grandmother of hulls
betterquesting.desc: I told you!

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Better safe than sorry!
betterquesting.desc: You should make some extra gear ... for ... when ... you know. Humans have proven to be stupid at times and die.

betterquesting.name: Im a Scrapman!
betterquesting.desc: Traces found on Venus show it has a high potential to create a catalyst we can make use of.

betterquesting.name: It doesnt even matter fabricator!
betterquesting.desc: Energy, Scrap, some space fabric and time and we will have ... pink matter!

betterquesting.name: Give me fuel
betterquesting.desc: Gimme me fuel, gimme fire, gimme what I desire!

betterquesting.name: Efficiency is key
betterquesting.desc: This will lower the fuel use alot!

betterquesting.name: Heal, DD and ...
betterquesting.desc: ... tank! We need a tank!

betterquesting.name: Take control
betterquesting.desc: This is a multiblock we are building! Of course we need a controller!

betterquesting.name: The sky is the limit!
betterquesting.desc: This will push the efficiency even further, but its not cheap!

betterquesting.name: This smell like teen gasoline
betterquesting.desc: Now that we have a tank, we need a way to fill it!

betterquesting.name: You spin my head right round
betterquesting.desc: Lets start with some cheap turbines to get this beauty up and running!

betterquesting.name: Every step you take
betterquesting.desc: Every spin you make, i'll be powering you. This is a small step for a turbine, but a big step for the energy production!

betterquesting.name: Trust me, im an engineer!
betterquesting.desc: They said its no good if turbines vibrate. Hah! Prove them wrong! (There are also the enderium and alloy turbines if you prefer them, but this quest wants a vibrant one)

betterquesting.name: Dense energy storage
betterquesting.desc: That thing in the basement. I think I can even improve it further!

betterquesting.name: Number one, energy!
betterquesting.desc: So you built a generator. Lets start up some of my auxialliary systems!

betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Fuel is pumping engine
betterquesting.desc: Well that shiny new generator runs best on fuel. We should search the planets for a better source of oil and refine it.

betterquesting.name: Moon Trance
betterquesting.desc: Start here

betterquesting.name: Stars align
betterquesting.desc: Your journey though the universe starts here

betterquesting.name: Elements
betterquesting.desc: Lasers, robots, pew pew

betterquesting.name: Crystallize
betterquesting.desc: Earl grey, hot!

betterquesting.name: Take flight
betterquesting.desc: MOAR POWA!

betterquesting.name: Improvements
betterquesting.desc: Little helpers

betterquesting.name: Transcendence
betterquesting.desc: Through the fabric of space and time
